This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image segmentation. The use of deep learning techniques and convolutional neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of an optimizer called AdamW, which is commonly used in Natural Language Processing (NLP) tasks, suggesting that it could also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the use of a systematic method to find the optimum learning rate suggests that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
